bug.short_desc: Wrong colors (Firefox on qemu-kvm with QXL driver)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1262196 strange colors on Firefox
Description of problem: Firefox doesn't render page's colors correctly, on Fedora 26 Workstation x86_64 (qemu-kvm guest, QXL driver). The session is the "Gnome Wayland" one.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): firefox-52.0-1.fc26.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Run Firefox
Actual results: Colors are messed up (see the attached screenshot)
Expected results: Colors should be displayed correctly
Additional info: Screenshot attached.

Please disregard this. A full system update via dnf, solved the issue.
I apologize for the inconvenience this may have caused.
